<div class="container">
    <h3>Rules and job instructions</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Manager can only view,edit anc cancel the reservations that user has made.</li>
        <li>Don't spread negative energy.</li>
        <li>Maintain open and effective communication with the car staff.</li>
        <li>Ensure the highest level of customer service and satisfaction.</li>
        <li>Manage and resolve guest complaints in a professional and timely manner.</li>
        <li>Adhere to all applicable laws, regulations, and industry standards.</li>
        <li>Maintain the security and confidentiality of guest information and car data.</li>
        <li>Monitor and optimize hotel operations to maximize revenue and profitability.</li>
        <li>Stay updated with industry trends and implement innovative strategies to enhance the hotel's competitiveness.</li>
        <li>Managerial Responsibilities - Managers are responsible for overseeing the day-to-day operations of the car rental business, including vehicle availability, staff management, and customer service.</li>
        <li>Reservation Management - Managers have the authority to approve, modify, or cancel reservations based on vehicle availability and company policies.</li>
        <li>Team Collaboration - Managers should foster a collaborative and supportive work environment, encouraging effective communication and teamwork among staff members.</li>
        <li>Performance Evaluation - Managers are responsible for evaluating the performance of car rental staff, providing constructive feedback, and implementing training programs as needed.</li>
        <li>Adherence to Regulations - Managers must ensure that the car rental business complies with all relevant laws, regulations, and industry standards.</li>
        <li>Decision-Making Authority - Managers have the authority to make decisions regarding fleet management, pricing adjustments, and strategic planning for the business.</li>
    </ul>

